Data Types in JavaScript

JavaScript is Dynamically typed i.e, You dont have to declare the  data type of the variable.

i. Primitive data type(base)
ii. Reference data type(Derived,Objects)

Primitive Data Types:
i. String: collection of characters
ii. Number: numbers
iii. Boolean: true/false
iv. null: intentional empty value
v. undefined: if you dont initialise the variable, undefined is the default value
vi. symbol: *later

Reference Data Types (HEAP memory allocation)
i. Arrays
ii. Functions
iii. Object literals
iv. Dates



